===Etymology===
First attested in 1600. From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|abstēmius||abstaining from wine}}; from {{m|la|ab|}}, {{m|la|abs||from}} + {{m|la|tēmus}}, root of {{m|la|tēmētum||[[intoxicating]] drink, mead, wine}}, akin to {{cog|de|dämlich||stupid, silly}}, {{cog|non|þám||mugginess}}, {{cog|sga|tám||death}}, {{cog|sa|ताम्यति||he becomes stunned, exhausted|tr=tāmyati}}.

